    dc:creator "Kanamori, Sally", "Kuro-O, Masaki", "Matsui, Masafumi", "Nishikawa, Kanto", "Niwa, Keita" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomic reassessment of salamanders (genus Hynobius) from Tsushima Islands Japan, with a resurrection of Hynobius tagoi Dunn, 1923 (Amphibia: Caudata)" ;
    bibo:endPage "236" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-08-30" ;
    bibo:startPage "201" ;
    bibo:volume "5339" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308968>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308972>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308980>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308984>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308988>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308992>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308994>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8309004>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8309006>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8309010> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308968>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map of Kyushu and its adjacent islands, Japan, showing the sampling localities of H. tsuensis (triangles), Hynobius sp. (inverse triangles), and H. nebulosus (circles) used for the morphological and microsatellite (SSR) analyses (open: morphological analysis, filled: both morphological and SSR analyses). Numbers correspond to pop no. in Table 2. The colored ranges indicate the distributional range of H. tsuensis (red, solid) and Hynobius sp. (blue, horizontal lines) in Tsushima Islands, and range of H. nebulosus (yellow, solid) in Kyushu. A dashed line in Tsushima Islands indicates the boundary between the northern (Kamijima) and southern islands (Shimojima), and a star in the Shimojima shows the center of Izuhara which is considered to be the type locality of H. tsuensis. A diamond in Kyushu indicates the type locality of H. nebulosus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8308968/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308972>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Phylogenetic tree for 34 Hynobius species and out groups based on the complete cyt b gene sequences (1141 bp) of mtDNA by the Bayesian inference method. The numbers at nodes indicate Bayesian posterior probability (BPP). Asterisks (*) indicate significant supports with BPP of 0.95 or higher." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8308972/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308980>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Dorsal and ventral views, and left side of the tail of a male topotypic (A, B, E; KUHE 58983) and a female topotypic specimens (C, D, F; KUHE 58709) of H. tagoi (Hynobius sp.) from Kamitsushima. A scale bar shows 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8308980/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308984>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Vomerine teeth series of a male neotype of H. tsuensis (A: KUHE 58656) from Izuhara, male topotypic specimens of H. tagoi (Hynobius sp.) (B: KUHE 58983) from Kamitsushima, and H. nebulosus (C: KUHE 58662) from Nagasaki City. Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8308984/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308988>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Boxplots showing maximum egg-sac length (MAESL), MAESL/ESW (egg-sac width), clutch size (CS), and unfertilized egg rate of four groups." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8308988/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308992>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Histograms showing length of the whiptail structure (WTL) of egg-sacs of H. tsuensis (A), Hynobius sp. (H. tagoi) (B), H. nebulosus from Nagasaki (C) and Fukue Island (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8308992/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8308994>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. A pair of egg sacs of H. tsuensis (A: KUHE 58986) from Kamitsushima, H. tagoi (Hynobius sp.) (B: KUHE 58669) from Kamitsushima, and H. nebulosus (C: KUHE 61872) from Nagasaki City. A white bar indicates 30 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8308994/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8309004>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Dorsal (A), ventral (B), and lateral (C: right, D: left) views of male holotype of H. tagoi (CAS 26563). A white bar shows 10 mm. Photo by Erica J. Ely." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8309004/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8309006>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Dorsal, lateral, and ventral views of a larva of H. tsuensis (A–C: KUHE 65029) from Izuhara and H. tagoi (D–F; KUHE 65028) from Toyotama. A white bar shows 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8309006/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8309010>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. An alive male (A: KUHE 63959), a pair of egg-sacs (B: KUHE 60144), a larva (C: not captured), and breeding habitat (D) of H. tagoi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8309010/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

